[normal]Sir Bob [bold]Kerslake[bold]: No.
[normal] 
[normal]It is really important to say that the demand side has had the profile recently in the press, but there is a huge amount going on 
[normal]on
[normal] the supply side in relation to large sites, infrastructure, funding, and support by way of affordable housing, so there is a whole raft of things that are happening on the supply side, and have been for a number of years.
[normal] 
[normal]I do not think you should see this as an agenda where it is just about the demand side.
[normal] 
[normal]I would also say—just adding to Peter’s answer—that what we are seeing now in terms of things like house prices is generally to do with rising market confidence.
[normal] 
[normal]It is not to do with the Help to Buy scheme; that is quite clear.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Q104 [bold]&#xa0; 
